  "response_text": "Celebrating Lunar New Year with a healthy, low-sodium twist is a wonderful idea! Here’s a suggested menu that maintains the essence of traditional dishes while being mindful of sodium levels:\n\n### Healthy Lunar New Year Dinner Menu\n\n#### Appetizer\n**Steamed Vegetable Dumplings**\n- Fill with a mix of finely chopped napa cabbage, shiitake mushrooms, carrots, and scallions. Use ginger and garlic for flavor, and serve with a low-sodium dipping sauce made from rice vinegar and a splash of sesame oil.\n\n#### Main Course\n**Herb-Infused Ginger Soy Chicken**\n- Use skinless chicken breast marinated in a mixture of low-sodium soy sauce, fresh ginger, garlic, and a splash of rice vinegar. Bake or grill the chicken until cooked through and serve sliced over a bed of steamed bok choy and spinach.\n\n**Stir-Fried Brown Rice with Vegetables**\n- Cook brown rice and stir-fry with a colorful mix of bell peppers, snap peas, carrots, and broccoli. Season with low-sodium soy sauce and a sprinkle of sesame seeds. Add a hint of garlic and fresh herbs like cilantro for added flavor.\n\n#### Side Dish\n**Braised Tofu with Mushrooms and Greens**\n- Use firm tofu, marinated in a low-sodium soy sauce and ginger mixture. Sauté with shiitake mushrooms and kale or bok choy until tender. Top with a sprinkle of sesame oil for richness.\n\n#### Dessert\n**Fresh Fruit Platter**\n- Celebrate with a vibrant assortment of seasonal fruits like mandarin oranges, kiwi, pomegranate seeds, and dragon fruit, symbolizing prosperity and good luck.\n\n#### Beverage\n**Jasmine Tea**\n- Serve hot jasmine tea, which is aromatic and refreshing, perfectly complementing the meal.\n\n### Tips for Preparation:\n- Use fresh herbs and spices to enhance flavors without adding salt.\n- Opt for cooking methods like steaming, grilling, or baking instead of frying.\n- Always taste as you go, adjusting flavors with acidity (like lemon or vinegar) rather than salt.\n\nThis menu reflects the traditional elements of a Lunar New Year feast while promoting a healthier lifestyle. Enjoy your celebration!",
